                        <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>κα</orig> <space extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty locus="name" match=".."/></space>
                        </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>               
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraduisible.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraducibile.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>غير قابل للترجمه بشكل جيد</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The very scanty information about this small fragment does not allow to restore its meaning. The editor's transcription seems to take the 
                two letters as the end of a word. No similar ending helps to guess which word. Conversely, we might have here the central syllable of the word for 'tithe' 
                (see <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr004200</ref>).</p>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
